15
00:00:33.020 --> 00:00:36.020
The first reason is staying on trend.

16
00:00:36.020 --> 00:00:37.020
I'm sure you've noticed

17
00:00:37.020 --> 00:00:39.060
that many recent websites and mobile apps

18
00:00:39.060 --> 00:00:40.090
are designed to give users

19
00:00:40.090 --> 00:00:43.060
the field of constant interactivity.

20
00:00:43.060 --> 00:00:47.010
Think of apps like chat apps, collaboration platforms,

21
00:00:47.010 --> 00:00:49.050
even social media platforms.

22
00:00:49.050 --> 00:00:52.020
These are all examples of where real-time app features

23
00:00:52.020 --> 00:00:55.000
are not only the trend but the expectation.

24
00:00:55.000 --> 00:00:57.040
If you plan to build an app that is similar to these,

25
00:00:57.040 --> 00:00:59.030
then you wanna be sure to learn what it takes

26
00:00:59.030 --> 00:01:01.020
to create real-time apps.

27
00:01:01.020 --> 00:01:03.070
Second is job readiness.

28
00:01:03.070 --> 00:01:05.050
If you're joining the development team

29
00:01:05.050 --> 00:01:07.040
that's working on a real-time app

30
00:01:07.040 --> 00:01:11.070
or has a real-time app in its portfolio of apps to maintain,

31
00:01:11.070 --> 00:01:14.070
you need to understand something about the major technology

32
00:01:14.070 --> 00:01:18.070
and APIs involved in creating these kinds of apps.

33
00:01:18.070 --> 00:01:21.040
Third, new challenges.

34
00:01:21.040 --> 00:01:23.030
Maybe you've never created an app

35
00:01:23.030 --> 00:01:26.010
that involved features with real-time web client

36
00:01:26.010 --> 00:01:28.000
and web server interaction.

37
00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:31.000
Maybe you're ready to do some proactive preparation

38
00:01:31.000 --> 00:01:33.050
for a future job opportunity.

39
00:01:33.050 --> 00:01:36.090
Number four, ideal user experiences.

40
00:01:36.090 --> 00:01:38.040
For certain types of apps,

